Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press).

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%grams} into thirds.

Pat the @sea bass fillets{2}, dry with #kitchen paper. Lay the fish, skin-side down, on a lined #baking tray.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over the @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} and drizzle over the @red pepper chilli jelly{25%grams}. Spread the mixture over the flesh with the back of a #spoon.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Bake the fish on the middle shelf until cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of water, then cover with a #lid (or foil) and allow to cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share your glazed sea bass to your #serving plates{}.

Serve with your spiced potatoes and garlic broccoli alongside.

Add a dollop of @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} for dipping.

Enjoy!